UNIT 4 â€“ Application of Threat Modelling Techniques
Unit Overview

This unit applied threat modelling techniques using practical tools such as the OWASP Threat Modeling Cookbook and the MITRE ATT&CK framework.

Artefacts

Threat model diagram

Workshop activity responses

MITRE ATT&CK mapping

Individual Contribution

I developed a threat model based on the workshop scenario and evaluated publicly available threat modelling tools.

Reflection

Applying threat modelling tools revealed their strengths and limitations. While frameworks like MITRE ATT&CK provide structured threat intelligence, they require contextual understanding to remain effective. This unit reinforced that tooling alone cannot replace analyst judgement, particularly in complex socio-technical systems.

References

MITRE (2023). ATT&CK Framework.
https://attack.mitre.org

OWASP (2021). Threat Modeling Cookbook.
https://owasp.org
